-Nerys~

@6266=~Tome of Profane Ascendence~
@6267=~You recovered this tome from within a dark Bhaalist Ossuary. Within its musty pages are the most secretive rites to Bhaal, including methods of vivisection and ritual sacrifice that are noted to best honor the Lord of Murder. You sense that while such a book would have an unholy presence in the past, Bhaal's death has left it in a diminished state, no more foul than the text and diagrams within.

A quick scan through reveals that many of the pages deeper in the book seem odd. There are stains of blood all over the pages, yet they contain no text that you can see. Even still, they seem important. Perhaps someone more familiar with the rites of Bhaal will know what to do with them.~

@6268=~Vivisectionist Blade~
@6269=~While many of Bhaal's cult believed that their lord cared little for how one suffered before death, only that it was the moment of their death that honored their lord, others believed that Bhaal admired the art of drawing out those last moments to exquisite suffering. The Vivisectionist's Blade was a tool carried by the higher priests of Bhaal committed to this philosophy, its razor shape honed specifically not to kill quickly, but to flense off pieces of their sacrifices bit by bit. The result is a fearsome weapon even when wielded away from the vivisectionist's table.

STATISTICS:

25% chance on hit to leave a target crippled in pain, stunning them for 6 seconds unless they save vs death.

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d6+2 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 5 Strength

Weight: 2~

@6271=~Cythandria's Note~
@6272=~To the one who killed me,

You're probably reading this looking to see if I had given you a nice simply synopsis of my thoughts and feelings, maybe what brought me to this point. Maybe this could have been useful to you, or maybe you just wanted to gloat on how you stopped me.

I refuse to give you that satisfaction. My hatred for you will continue past my death. I will be there for your every failure, your every misfortune and loss. And I will be laughing at you.

I curse you. May your limbs wither away and your senses flee you. May you be abandoned by everyone who was ever dear to you, and be left to live as a forgotten, unloved husk. You don't deserve it. I didn't, and you deserve even less.

Bastard. Do you think I'm petty? Maybe I am. I don't care. Nothing matters, none of it.

PS: If you're not the one who killed me, well, I mean this for you too anyway.~

@6531=~Stiletto of Shifting Light~
@6532=~Light never seems to quite reflect cleanly the blade of this dagger, always instead being caught and bent in strange angles. This makes any reflections that come from it appear twisted and warped. Such daggers are most common among illusionist assassins who utilize their spells to get in close to a target and strike, then to use the confusion from their spells to allow them to escape. 

This particular dagger weaves a combination of two such spells that activates when struck. The first causes the refracted light around them to form an identical illusory copy nearby, while the second renders them invisible from sight.

