@6533=~Remembrance~
@6534=~This metallic staff is capped with a large sapphire gem that shines in a short radius around it. It was the craft of an oddly forgetful wizard who became frustrated when he would misremember the very spells he had spent all night studying the next morning. Onlookers questioned little why the wizard had a slippery memory however, as he was prone to knocking himself on the head with his own staff during moments of frustration. His enchantment at least let such self-punitive quirks undo as much harm as they did, though it often left him forgetting one spell as he remembered another. 

He eventually passed on his staff to a priest of Tempus who was a dear friend of his in his later years. She discovered that using the staff to clobber the heads of monsters did the trick far better than smacking one's own.

