@7136=~Damp Note~
@7137=~<CHARNAME>,

This shouldn't come as too much of a surprise. Truth is, the wound I suffered from Sarevok was always fatal, I simply had bought a few more months of time. But that time has run out. This glade seems a peaceful enough place to pass. I enjoy the quiet. I've already ingested the poison pill. This is my last message to you.

The Deathbringer ritual is a sham. Or... a ruse perpetuated by the Bhaal Priests to control those who proved themselves the most efficient weapons. Yet I now realize Sarevok never finished the ritual. He was ever his own man. I sought a truth that would easily explain our fall, but the truth has proven to be both elusive as well as clear and plain.

We were undone because you were simply better than us. 

Gloat if you like, I acknowledge your victory, absolute. I've even left you my best pair of shoes as a reward. How kind am I?

Do not let yourself be guided by those who would use you. 

-Winski Perorate~